issue.title: Failed to build onnxruntime with TensorRT on Windows 11

labels.name: ep:TensorRT
labels.description: issues related to TensorRT execution provider

repository.name: onnxruntime
repository.description: ONNX Runtime: cross-platform, high performance ML inferencing and training accelerator

issue.body:
**Describe the bug**
I am unable to build onnxruntime with TensorRT provider after following all of the given instructions. The issue is similar to [this](https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/issues/3630) and [this](https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/issues/4741), but what is suggested there does not work for me. I have also set `Language for non-Unicode programs` to English as suggested in the latter issue.
I was able to build successfully about a year ago with older versions, following the same steps, but now it does not work.

**Urgency**
No urgency, but I've been trying to build the newest version for a several days now, trying out various options to no success.

**System information**
- OS Platform and Distribution (e.g., Linux Ubuntu 16.04): `Windows 11`
- ONNX Runtime installed from (source or binary): `source`
- ONNX Runtime version: master from commit [0e85af6](https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/commit/0e85af6990ac41b8925722d4aee990909421a729)
- Python version: `3.9`
- Visual Studio version (if applicable): `VS 2019`
- GCC/Compiler version (if compiling from source): -
- CUDA/cuDNN version: `CUDA 11.4.4`, `cuDNN 8.2.4` as suggested [here](https://onnxruntime.ai/docs/build/eps.html#tensorrt)
- TensorRT version: `TensorRT-8.2.3.0`
- GPU model and memory: Nvidia GeForce RTX 2060 with Max-Q Design 6 GB

**To Reproduce**
- `git clone --recursive https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime.git`
- `cd onnxruntime`
- `build.bat --config Release --build_shared_lib --cudnn_home "C:\Program Files\NVIDIA GPU Computing Toolkit\CUDA\v11.4" --cuda_home "C:\Program Files\NVIDIA GPU Computing Toolkit\CUDA\v11.4" --use_tensorrt --tensorrt_home "C:\Libraries\TensorRT-8.2.3.0" --cuda_version 11.4 --cmake_generator "Visual Studio 16 2019"`

**Expected behavior**
Successfully build onnxruntime with TensorRT execution provider

**Screenshots**
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/36015059/181648633-25a5a38a-d55c-4768-8d8a-6dd0819bb95d.png)


**Additional context**
- Changing `--config` and removing `--build_shared_lib` does not help
- I tried both `--cmake_generator "Visual Studio 16 2019"` and `--cmake_generator "Visual Studio 17 2022"`, the latter fails with a different error in the beginning of the script
